# CODEOWNERS — team ownership for skills in this catalog
#
# Purpose: let teams own their own skills without a central maintainer
# becoming a review bottleneck. GitHub automatically requests review
# from the listed owners when a PR touches a matching path.
#
# Rules (GitHub semantics):
# - The LAST matching rule wins, so put specific rules below general ones.
# - Paths without an owner still require review, but from the default owners.
# - Teams must be written as `@<org>/<team-slug>`; individuals as `@<user>`.
# - Keep one skill per line; do not group multiple skill folders on one rule.
#
# See CONTRIBUTING.md ("Team ownership") for how to claim or transfer a skill.

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Defaults — Platform Engineering owns anything not claimed by a specific team.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
*                         @<org>/<platform-engineering>

# Shared infrastructure — only Platform Engineering changes the CLI, CI, or the contract.
/src/                     @<org>/<platform-engineering>
/test/                    @<org>/<platform-engineering>
/.github/                 @<org>/<platform-engineering>
/CONTRIBUTING.md          @<org>/<platform-engineering>
/README.md                @<org>/<platform-engineering>
/AGENTS.md                @<org>/<platform-engineering>

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Per-skill ownership — one line per skill, grouped by owning team.
# Add a new line when you contribute a skill; remove yours when you hand it off.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Platform Engineering — horizontal retrieval utility used by other skills.
/skills/context7-docs/              @<org>/<platform-engineering>

# Security — owns changelog-driven review of third-party bumps.
/skills/dependency-bump-reviewer/   @<org>/<security-team>

# Example: Multiple owners (both teams must approve)
# /skills/release-notes/            @<org>/<platform-team> @<org>/<docs-team>
